            "title": "Lifco Reports Higher Revenue and Net Profit in Q3",
            "description": "<div class=\"txt-s4 article-text\"><span class=\"generated_text\">\nIndustrial conglomerate Lifco has posted higher-than-expected revenue for the third quarter, with net profit also on the rise.<br/><br/>\nRevenue increased by 8.9 percent to SEK 6,842 million (6,282). This outcome exceeded Bloomberg's analyst consensus, which was SEK 6,577 million. Organic sales growth reached 4.3 percent (1.9).<br/><br/>\nEBITA amounted to SEK 1,543 million (1,388), with an EBITA margin of 22.6 percent (22.1). According to Bloomberg, expectations for adjusted EBITA stood at SEK 1,453 million.<br/><br/>\nProfit before tax was SEK 1,124 million (1,020). Net profit totaled SEK 900 million (757). Earnings per share amounted to SEK 1.96 (5.14).<br/><br/>\nCash flow from operating activities reached SEK 1,394 million (1,210).<br/><br/>\nLifco CEO Per Waldermarson commented on the company's acquisition opportunities:<br/><br/>\n\"Lifco continues to maintain a strong financial position, with net interest-bearing debt at 1.3 times EBITDA as of September 30, 2025, which is well within our target of a maximum of three times EBITDA. This means Lifco has the financial capacity to pursue further acquisitions.\"\n</span><br/><table class=\"table txt-s2 mt-20 mb-10 table--small table--all_bordered\"><tbody><tr><td>\n            Lifco, SEK million</td><td>\n            Q3-2025 </td><td>\n            Consensus</td><td>\n            Change vs. Consensus</td><td>\n            Q3-2024 </td><td>\n            Change</td></tr><tr><td>\n            Net Revenue</td><td>\n             6,842 </td><td>\n             6,577 </td><td>\n             4.0%</td><td>\n             6,282 </td><td>\n             8.9%</td></tr><tr><td>\n            Organic Sales Growth, %</td><td>\n             4.3 </td><td></td><td></td><td>\n             1.9 </td><td>\n             126.3%</td></tr><tr><td>\n            EBITA</td><td>\n             1,543 </td><td></td><td></td><td>\n             1,388 </td><t