        {
            "title": "Norsk Hydro's Adjusted Earnings Fall Short of Expectations",
            "description": "<div class=\"txt-s4 article-text\"><span class=\"generated_text\">Norwegian aluminum producer Norsk Hydro reported higher-than-expected revenue for the third quarter, but its adjusted operating profit came in significantly below forecasts.<br/><br/>\nRevenue rose 0.9 percent to NOK 50,546 million (50,089), exceeding the company's analyst consensus of NOK 47,943.<br/><br/>\nAdjusted EBITDA amounted to NOK 5,996 million (7,367), falling short of the expected NOK 6,366, with an adjusted EBITDA margin of 11.9 percent (14.7).<br/><br/>\nOperating profit reached NOK 3,491 million (3,488). The operating margin was 6.9 percent (7.0).<br/><br/>\nAdjusted operating profit came in at NOK 3,510 million (4,944), compared to the expected NOK 3,873, with an adjusted operating margin of 6.9 percent (9.9).<br/><br/>\nNet profit after tax was NOK 2,149 million (1,409).<br/><br/>\nAdjusted earnings per share stood at NOK 1.02 (1.49).<br/><br/>\n\"Challenging markets impacted our third quarter, and we are seeing weaker results. Despite the lower adjusted EBITDA, I am pleased to report solid cash generation as we continue to deliver results in our efficiency and improvement initiatives to enhance robustness,\" said Eivind Kallevik, CEO of Norsk Hydro.\n</span><br/><table class=\"table txt-s2 mt-20 mb-10 table--small table--all_bordered\"><tbody><tr><td>\n            Norsk Hydro, MNOK</td><td>\n            Q3-2025 </td><td>\n            Consensus</td><td>\n            Change vs Consensus</td><td>\n            Q3-2024 </td><td>\n            Change</td></tr><tr><td>\n            Net Revenue</td><td>\n             50,546 </td><td>\n             47,943 </td><td>\n             5.4%</td><td>\n             50,089 </td><td>\n             0.9%</td></tr><tr><td>\n            Adjusted EBITDA</td><td>\n             5,996 </td><td>\n             6,366 </td><td>\n            -5.8%</td><td>\n             7,367 </td><td>\n            -18.6%</td></tr><tr><td>\n            Adju